text: Orexana ultima is a species of air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Geomitridae, the hairy snails and their allies; the species is endemic to Fuerteventura island (Canary Islands). Orexana ultima Lomo del Aceituno, Fuerteventura (Las Palmas). Scale bar 0.5 cm. == References == Category:Molluscs
title: Orexana ultima
